title: High Vitamin A Supplementation Coverage
description: In 2022, Guinea achieved a remarkable Vitamin A supplementation coverage rate of 97% among children aged 6-59 months, indicating strong public health initiatives.

title: Low Female Representation in Secondary Education
description: As of 2021, only 5.8% of secondary education teachers in Guinea were female, highlighting a significant gender disparity in the education sector.

title: Minimal Travel Service Imports
description: In 2022, travel services accounted for just 1.1% of Guinea's commercial service imports, reflecting limited international travel engagement.

title: Low Physician Density
description: Guinea had only 0.021 physicians per 1,000 people in 2022, indicating a critical shortage of medical professionals in the country.

title: Negligible International Tourism Receipts
description: In 2020, international tourism receipts contributed a mere 0.014% to Guinea's total exports, suggesting limited tourism revenue.

title: Significant Financial Intermediary Services
description: Guinea's financial intermediary services indirectly measured reached 3.66 trillion LCU in current terms in 2022, showcasing a robust financial sector.

title: Low Ores and Metals Import Dependency
description: In 2016, ores and metals constituted only 30.9% of Guinea's merchandise imports, indicating a diversified import portfolio.
